Module comp3111.examsystem
Package comp3111.examsystem.entity

Class Record

java.lang.Object
comp3111.examsystem.entity.Entity
comp3111.examsystem.entity.Record
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Entity>
public class Record extends Entity
Represents a record in the examination system that associates a specific question with an exam. This class stores the keys for both the question and the exam, and provides methods to retrieve additional information about the associated exam and question such as their names, types, and scores. The `Record` class allows for querying the exam and question details based on their respective keys stored within the record.

      public String getExamName()
      Retrieves the name of the exam associated with this record. The method queries the `Exam` database using the `examKey` stored in the record and returns the name of the corresponding exam. If the exam is not found, it returns `null`.
      Returns:
      The name of the exam associated with the record, or `null` if the exam cannot be found.
